  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1240 mg
author: Michelle Doll Olson
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/gnocchi-with-spinach-tomatoes-5e839cd0c454bc698b557f71
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 20 minutes
---

Bring a #medium pot{} of @salted water{} to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Halve @Heirloom Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce}.

Melt @Butter{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and cook, stirring, until golden and toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in half the @Garlic Powder{1%tsp} (you'll use the rest later) and cook until just fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{} and season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Wipe out pan.

> For 4 servings: use 2 TBSP butter instead of 1 TBSP.

Once water is boiling, add @Gnocchi{8.8%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Drain.

Meanwhile, melt @Butter{1%tbsp} in pan used for panko over medium-high heat. Add remaining garlic powder and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @water{1/3%cup}, @Veggie Stock Concentrate{1}, and @Cream Cheese{4%tbsp}. Bring to a simmer, stirring, until combined and creamy, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

> For 4 servings: use 2 TBSP butter and ½ cup water.

Stir tomatoes and @Spinach{5%ounce} into pan with sauce. Cook, stirring, until spinach is wilted and tomatoes are softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir gnocchi into pan with sauce until thoroughly coated. If needed, add a splash or two of water. Taste and season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Divide gnocchi between #bowls{} and top with @Parmesan Cheese{1/4%cup}. Sprinkle with as much garlic panko as you like. Add a pinch of @Chili Flakes{1%tsp} to taste and serve.